The Amajuba district mayor has welcomed government's assistance to help communities get back on their feet. DURBAN - The Amajuba district mayor has welcomed government's assistance to help communities get back on their feet. This after yet another tornado ripped through the Utrecht area on Friday night. It was the third tornado to hit KwaZulu-Natal in the space of one month. READ: Tornado hits Utrecht The first one caused extensive damage in New Hanover and the second was confirmed in Bergville. District mayor Musa Ngubane said they need help to reconstruct damaged houses and also for food for the families affected.